+>---------------------<+
| Skicker LoggerManager |
+>---------------------<+

Logger configurer for the excellent log4javascript.
Creates loggers on demand from given configurations.

see. src/Skicker/LoggerManager.ts for usage example



+>--------------<+
|  Dependencies  |
+>--------------<+

Tested on node versions:

    v9.3.0 - 2018.01.17
    v8.9.4 - 2018.01.17



+>-------------<+
|  Example app  |
+>-------------<+

Execute

    npm install
    npm run dev

to install missing dependencies and start a dev-server.

Go to

    localhost:5000

to see the app.



+>----------------------<+
| Building a new version |
+>----------------------<+

To distribute an updated version of this module, do the following:

1. Run tests

Start test runner server

    npm run test

Go to localhost:5001
And verify that all test pass in the jasmine-html reporter

Fix broken tests

2. Package for distribution

    npm run compile

3. Commit changes to Git

    VERSION=0.0.2 npm run release

4. Push to master

    git push origin master --tags



+>--------------------------------------<+
| Using the dependency in another module |
+>--------------------------------------<+

    npm install -S "git+ssh://git@skicker.fi:~/repos/skicker-logger-manager.git"

You probably need to input your ssh-key passphrase to proceed.

